# visualising missing and non-missing values for each columns

not_null_count = np.array([])
nan_count = np.array([])

for column in df.columns:
    not_null_count = np.append(not_null_count, df[column].count())
    nan_count = np.append(nan_count, df[column].isnull().sum())

fig, ax = plt.subplots(1,1,figsize = (22,12))

ax.bar(column_names, pd.Series(not_null_count),label= 'Non missing values', color='teal', edgecolor='black')
ax.bar(column_names, pd.Series(nan_count),label= 'Missing Values', bottom=not_null_count, color='lightgreen', edgecolor='black')
ax.tick_params(axis='x', rotation=90)
ax.tick_params(axis='both', labelsize=14)
ax.set_title("No of missing and non missing values for each columns", fontsize=17)
ax.set_ylabel("No of observations", fontsize=15)

plt.legend(prop= {'size':18})
plt.show()

In [6]:
# remove extra whitespaces
df = df.applymap(lambda column:column.strip() if type(column) == str else column)

# check physically impossible values, other typos, incorrect capitalisation
for column in df.columns:
    if(df[column].dtypes != 'float64'):
        df[column] = df[column].replace('(\t)*(\?)*', '', regex = True)
In [7]:
# correcting data types of columns
df['packed cell volume'] = pd.to_numeric(df['packed cell volume'])
df['red blood cell count'] = pd.to_numeric(df['red blood cell count'])
df['white blood cell count'] = pd.to_numeric(df['white blood cell count'])

#for column in df.columns:
#    if df[column].dtypes == 'float64':
#        df[column].fillna(round(df[column].mean(), 0), inplace = True)
#        df[column].replace(to_replace = '', value = round(df[column].mean(), 0), inplace = True)
#    elif df[column].dtypes == 'object':
#        df[column].fillna(df[column].mode().iloc[0], inplace = True)

# replace missing values - Imputation
# columns to impute with less than 18% missing values in total
to_replace_mean = ['age', 'blood pressure', 'packed cell volume']
to_replace_mode = ['specific gravity', 'albumin', 'sugar', 'pus cell', 'pus cell clumps', 'bacteria', 'hypertension', 
                   'diabetes mellitus', 'coronary artery disease', 'appetite', 'pedal edema', 'anemia']
te_replace_median = ['blood glucose random', 'blood urea', 'serum creatinine', 'hemoglobin']

for column in to_replace_mean:
    df[column].fillna(round(df[column].mean(), 1), inplace = True)
for column in te_replace_median:
    df[column].fillna(df[column].median(), inplace = True)
for column in to_replace_mode:
    df[column].fillna(df[column].mode().iloc[0], inplace = True)
    
# columns - red blood cells, sodium, potassium, white blood cell count and red blood cell count have 20-35% missing values, 
# so rather than imputing we will be replacing NaNs with -1 (an impossible value denoting that the data is not present)
to_replace_negative = ['red blood cells', 'sodium', 'potassium', 'white blood cell count', 'red blood cell count']
for column in to_replace_negative:
    df[column].fillna(-1, inplace = True)

### categories for different columns (performing sanity checks on columns by 
# converting into NaNs for other than these values)
yes_no_category = ['yes', 'no']
specific_gravity_category = [1.005, 1.01, 1.015, 1.02, 1.025]
albumin_sugar_category = [0., 1., 2., 3., 4., 5.]
normal_abnormal_category = ['normal', 'abnormal']
rbc_category = ['normal', 'abnormal', -1]
present_notpresent_category = ['present', 'notpresent']
apetite_category = ['good', 'poor']
class_category = ['ckd', 'notckd']

# correcting data types of columns
df['age'] = df['age'].astype('int64')
df['blood pressure'] = df['blood pressure'].astype('int64')
df['albumin'] = df['albumin'].astype(pd.api.types.CategoricalDtype(categories=albumin_sugar_category))
df['sugar'] = df['sugar'].astype(pd.api.types.CategoricalDtype(categories=albumin_sugar_category))
df['specific gravity'] = df['specific gravity'].astype(pd.api.types.CategoricalDtype(categories=specific_gravity_category))
df['red blood cells'] = df['red blood cells'].astype(pd.api.types.CategoricalDtype(categories=rbc_category))
df['pus cell'] = df['pus cell'].astype(pd.api.types.CategoricalDtype(categories=normal_abnormal_category))
df['pus cell clumps'] = df['pus cell clumps'].astype(pd.api.types.CategoricalDtype(categories=present_notpresent_category))
df['bacteria'] = df['bacteria'].astype(pd.api.types.CategoricalDtype(categories=present_notpresent_category))
df['blood glucose random'] = df['blood glucose random'].astype('int64')
df['blood urea'] = df['blood urea'].astype('int64')
df['sodium'] = df['sodium'].astype('int64')
df['packed cell volume'] = df['packed cell volume'].astype('int64')
df['white blood cell count'] = df['white blood cell count'].astype('int64')
df['hypertension'] = df['hypertension'].astype(pd.api.types.CategoricalDtype(categories=yes_no_category))
df['diabetes mellitus'] = df['diabetes mellitus'].astype(pd.api.types.CategoricalDtype(categories=yes_no_category))
df['coronary artery disease'] = df['coronary artery disease'].astype(pd.api.types.CategoricalDtype(categories=yes_no_category))
df['appetite'] = df['appetite'].astype(pd.api.types.CategoricalDtype(categories=apetite_category))
df['pedal edema'] = df['pedal edema'].astype(pd.api.types.CategoricalDtype(categories=yes_no_category))
df['anemia'] = df['anemia'].astype(pd.api.types.CategoricalDtype(categories=yes_no_category))
df['class'] = df['class'].astype(pd.api.types.CategoricalDtype(categories=class_category))

# 2.2 Analysing relationship between 'blood pressure' and 'class' columns
# Hypothesis: High blood pressure is the second leading cause of CKD. Like high blood glucose, high blood pressure also 
# can damage the blood vessels in your kidneys. Almost 1 in 5 adults with high blood pressure has CKD

# defining data
# getting average bp values for ckd and non-ckd patients
blood_pressure_values = [df[df['class'] == 'ckd']['blood pressure'].mean(), 
                         df[df['class'] == 'notckd']['blood pressure'].mean()]
# getting percentage of ckd patients with high bp (>= 80)
blood_pressure_pct = [df[(df['class'] == 'ckd') & (df['blood pressure'] >= 80)]['blood pressure'].shape[0] / df[df['class'] == 'ckd'].shape[0],
                     1 - (df[(df['class'] == 'ckd') & (df['blood pressure'] >= 80)]['blood pressure'].shape[0] / df[df['class'] == 'ckd'].shape[0])]

# create axes object for plotting the graph
fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(8, 4), dpi=100)

# plotting bar plot
bar_width = 0.3
x_labels = ['CKD', 'Not CKD']
axes[0].bar(x_labels, blood_pressure_values, bar_width, 
             color = ['crimson', 'gold'], edgecolor = 'black')

# setting y-axis label
axes[0].set_ylabel('Average Blood Pressure (mm/Hg)')
# setting grid lines
axes[0].grid(axis='y', linestyle='--')

# plotting pie chart
axes[1].pie(blood_pressure_pct, labels=['High BP (>= 80)', 'Normal BP (< 80)'],
            colors = ['red', 'lightgreen'], autopct='%1.0f%%',textprops={'fontsize': 12}, shadow = True)
axes[1].set_title('How many CKD patients \nhave high BP?', fontsize=14)

plt.tight_layout()

# 2.4 Analysing body diseases grouped by age groups

# create data such that it has total count for diseased people grouped by age groups
df_binned = df
# bin the 'age' column
df_binned['age group'] = pd.cut(df_binned['age'], bins=[-1, 18, 35, 50, 100], labels = ['0-18 years', '19-35 years', '36-50 years', '50+ years'])

data = [
    df_binned[df_binned['hypertension'] == 'yes'].groupby('age group')['hypertension'].count(),
    df_binned[df_binned['diabetes mellitus'] == 'yes'].groupby('age group')['diabetes mellitus'].count(),
    df_binned[df_binned['coronary artery disease'] == 'yes'].groupby('age group')['coronary artery disease'].count(),
    df_binned[df_binned['class'] == 'ckd'].groupby('age group')['class'].count(),
]

x_labels = ['0-18 years', '19-35 years', '36-50 years', '50+ years']

# setting bar width
bar_width = 0.1
bar_idx = list(range(len(x_labels)))

# colors to use
colors = ['gold','crimson','purple', 'navy']
labels = ['Hypertension', 'Diabetes Mellitus', 'Coronary Artery Disease', 'CKD']

# create axes object to plot the graph
fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 1, figsize=(15, 10), dpi=100)


# loop through every age group and increase the bar index every time to plot grouped bar chart
for index, data_col, color in zip(range(len(x_labels)), data, colors):
    axes.bar([idx + (index*bar_width) for idx in bar_idx], data_col, bar_width, 
             color = color, label = labels[index], edgecolor = 'black')
    
# age-group count
x_labels = ['0-18 years', '19-35 years', '36-50 years', '50+ years']
age_group_count = [df_binned[df_binned['age group']== '0-18 years'].shape[0],
 df_binned[df_binned['age group']== '19-35 years'].shape[0],
 df_binned[df_binned['age group']== '36-50 years'].shape[0],
 df_binned[df_binned['age group']== '50+ years'].shape[0]]

_label = 0
for index in range(len(x_labels)):
    _label = index
    axes.bar([idx + (index*bar_width) for idx in bar_idx], age_group_count, bar_width, 
             color = 'mistyrose', alpha=0.6, label= 'age group count' if _label == 0 else None)

# 2.6 What is the average 'rbc count', 'wbc count', 'sodium', 'potassium', 'blood glucose' levels based on age group

# create data such that it has average levels for each minerals/cells grouped by age groups
data = [
    # dropping missing values wherever required
    df_binned[df_binned['red blood cell count'] != -1].groupby('age group')['red blood cell count'].mean(),
    df_binned[df_binned['white blood cell count'] != -1].groupby('age group')['white blood cell count'].mean()/1000,
    df_binned[df_binned['sodium'] != -1].groupby('age group')['sodium'].mean()/10,
    df_binned[df_binned['potassium'] != -1].groupby('age group')['potassium'].mean(),
    df_binned.groupby('age group')['blood glucose random'].mean()/10,
]

x_labels = ['0-18 years', '19-35 years', '36-50 years', '50+ years']

# setting bar width
bar_width = 0.1
bar_idx = list(range(len(x_labels)))

# colors to use
colors = ['purple', 'violet' , 'gold', 'navy', 'red']
labels = ['RBC count', 'WBC count', 'Sodium levels', 'Potassium levels', 'Blood Glucose levels']
markers = ['*', 'o', '^', 's', 'p']

# create axes object to plot the graph
fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 1, figsize=(8, 5), dpi=100)


# loop through every age group and increase the bar index every time to plot grouped bar chart
for index, data_col, color in zip(range(len(data)), data, colors):
    axes.plot(x_labels, data_col, color = color, label = labels[index], marker=markers[index])

# setting y-axis label and title
axes.set_ylabel('Average\nRBC count (millions/cmm)\nWBC count (1000s per cmm)\nSodium (10s per mEq/L)\nPotassium (mEq/L)\nBlood Glucose (10s per mgs/dl)')
